article.description: UC Davis cruises to 75-69 win over Cal State Fullerton
article.headline: UC Davis cruises to 75-69 win over Cal State Fullerton
article.linkText: UC Davis cruises to 75-69 win over Cal State Fullerton
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Josh Fox sank all six of his shots from the field and finished with 18 points to lead UC Davis to a 75-69 win over Cal State Fullerton on Thursday night. Tyler Les scored 14 and Avery Johnson added 11 while Josh Ritchart and Brynton Lemar had 10 apiece for UC Davis (19-4, 9-1 Big West), which extended its win streak to five and got the season sweep over the Titans. The Aggies, who never trailed, hit 20 of 46 from the floor (43.5 percent) and held a 28-15 edge in made free throws. Fullerton (9-15, 1-8) cut the lead to 45-43 with Steve McClellan's tip-in at 10:09 in the second half but the Aggies took control with a 12-4 run that included three buckets from Fox to rebuild the margin it protected down the stretch. Alex Harris, Josh Gentry and Lanerryl Johnson led the Titans with 11 points apiece.
